    "body": "I had some progress on the specific issue.\r\n\r\nI found out that, instead of using ` ```mermaid ` to specify the graph, I can directly use ` <div class=\"mermaid\">` and include \r\n```html\r\n<script src=\"https://unpkg.com/mermaid/dist/mermaid.min.js\" crossorigin=\"anonymous\"></script>\r\n<script>mermaid.initialize({startOnLoad:true});</script>\r\n```\r\nanywhere in the EIP that will do it! Would be nice if this was done by `kramdown`.\r\n\r\nI figured out that `gitlab-kramdown` is much more featureful than vanilla `kramdown`, and even support `plantuml`.\r\n\r\nkramdown developer said that I could implement a module for syntax highlighter that could handle that ` ```mermaid `. \r\n\r\nI think that for short term solution, after merging an EIP, the editors should ask (or change themselves) this. \r\nAlso, EIP editors must be aware that is possible to inject javascript in an EIP file, and this will result in the script being run whenever that specific EIP page is loaded.",
