    "body": "> I figured out that gitlab-kramdown is much more featureful than vanilla kramdown, and even support plantuml.\r\n\r\nIt seems that [gitlab_kramdown](https://gitlab.com/gitlab-org/gitlab_kramdown) also has gitlab specific features and what I do not clearly understand yet it even has a setting like the below:\r\n> gitlab_url | https://gitlab.com | GitLab instance URL to build reference links\r\n\r\nCurrently *mostly* how the EIPs render on Github is identical to how they render on the eips.ethereum.org. Keeping this I think would be very useful, until we move off Github.\r\n\r\n> kramdown developer said that I could implement a module for syntax highlighter that could handle that ```mermaid.\r\n\r\nDid you by any chance made any progress on this?\r\n\r\nAlso instead of mermaid, potentially supporting graphviz is an alternative.",
